This paper is about semantic image segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and a domain transform (DT) filtering method. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks, specifically image segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of CNNs and machine learning techniques for image segmentation also suggests that the paper could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of domain transform filtering, which is a modern edge-preserving filtering method, suggests that the paper could also be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
